doc.ContractDescription: GOALS&OBJECTIVES WE PROPOSE TO CONDUCT STATE-OF-THE-ART EXPERIMENTS THAT WILL COMPRISE THE MOST SYSTEMATIC INVESTIGATION OF THE ROLE OF PARTICULATES ON THE RHEOLOGY OF WATER ICE TO DATE. USING A VARIETY OF NOVEL SAMPLE FABRICATION TECHNIQUES, COUPLED WITH VERY DETAILED MICROSTRUCTURAL DATA MADE AVAILABLE BY EXCITING, SOPHISTICATED NEW ELECTRON BACKSCATTER DIFFRACTION (EBSD) METHODS, WE WILL COMPLETE SYSTEMATIC STUDIES OF GRAIN BOUNDARY SLIDING (GBS) AND DISLOCATION CREEP FOR PURE AND PARTICULATE-BEARING ICES. MORE SPECIFICALLY, WE WILL RIGOROUSLY TEST THE FIELD-BOUNDARY HYPOTHESIS FOR PURE AND IMPURITY-BEARING ICE, WHEREBY FLOW IN PLANETARY AND GLACIOLOGICAL SETTINGS IS THEORIZED TO OCCUR VIA A DYNAMIC BALANCE BETWEEN GBS CREEP AND DISLOCATION CREEP. AN IMPORTANT GOAL OF THESE STUDIES IS TO DETERMINE WHETHER OR NOT GRAIN SIZE IS A FREE PARAMETER IN ICY PLANETARY ENVIRONMENTS, OR WHETHER IT REFLECTS THE AMBIENT CONDITIONS OF DEFORMATION. CRITICAL QUESTIONS WE WILL ADDRESS VIA OUR EXPERIMENTS ARE: (1) HOW DOES THE PRESENCE OF INTRAGRANULAR AND INTERGRANULAR IMPURITIES IN ICE INFLUENCE GBS CREEP AND DISLOCATION CREEP? (2) HOW DOES THE INFLUENCE OF IMPURITIES ON THESE CREEP MECHANISMS ALTER THE DYNAMIC BALANCE POSTULATED BY THE FIELD BOUNDARY HYPOTHESIS? (3) UNDER WHAT CONDITIONS DO IMPURITIES IMPEDE GRAIN GROWTH, AND IN WHAT MANNER DOES THIS ALTER THE DYNAMIC BALANCE BETWEEN GBS CREEP AND DISLOCATON CREEP? THE RESEARCH PROPOSED HERE MERGES A DECADES-LONG EXPERIMENTAL CAMPAIGN CONDUCTED BY THE CO-I AND COLLEAGUES WITH A NEWLY ESTABLISHED ICE PHYSICS RESEARCH PROGRAM AT THE UNIVERSITY OF PENNSYLVANIA. AS DETAILED BELOW, A MAJOR EMPHASIS IN THIS PROPOSAL IS ON EMPLOYING NEWLY AVAILABLE ANALYTICAL TECHNIQUES AS A COMPLEMENTARY MEANS OF DISCOVERING AND UNDERSTANDING PHYSICAL MECHANISMS OF DEFORMATION IN ICE.

doc.ContractDescription: A COMPREHENSIVE INVESTIGATION INTO MODELING SUPERNOVAE SPECTRA SUPERNOVAE ARE A RICH SOURCE OF INFORMATION. BY STUDYING THEIR LIGHT CURVES AND SPECTRA WE GAIN INSIGHTS INTO STELLAR EVOLUTION, THE NATURE OF THE PROGENITOR STAR, SURFACE ABUNDANCES AT THE TIME OF THE EXPLOSION, WHETHER PREVIOUS MASS-LOSS EPISODES HAVE OCCURRED, THE PHYSICS OF THE EXPLOSION INCLUDING THE AMOUNT AND TYPE OF ELEMENTS SYNTHESIZED, AND WHETHER THE EXPLOSION HAS PRODUCED SIGNIFICANT MIXING BETWEEN SHELLS OF DIFFERENT CHEMICAL COMPOSITION. TO MAXIMIZE THE INFORMATION THAT CAN BE GLEANED FROM OBSERVATIONS OF SUPERNOVAE IT IS ESSENTIAL THAT WE HAVE THE NECESSARY SPECTROSCOPIC TOOLS. TO THIS END, WE ARE DEVELOPING A CODE, CMFGEN, CAPABLE OF MODELING SUPERNOVA LIGHT CURVES AND SPECTRA. THE CODE IS CURRENTLY BEING USED, TO STUDY CORE-COLLAPSE SUPERNOVAE AS WELL AS THOSE ARISING FROM THE NUCLEAR DETONATION OF A WHITE DWARF STAR. WE WISH TO EXTEND CMFGEN'S CAPABILITIES BY DEVELOPING A PROCEDURE TO HANDLE NON-MONOTONIC VELOCITY FLOWS SO THAT WE CAN TREAT SHOCK BREAKOUT AND THE INTERACTION OF SUPERNOVA EJECTA WITH CIRCUMSTELLAR MATERIAL. WE WILL ALSO INVESTIGATE MAGNETAR-POWERED SNE, AND EXPLORE THE CONNECTION BETWEEN TYPE IB AND TYPE IC SUPERNOVAE AND THOSE SUPERNOVAE ASSOCIATED WITH LONG-DURATION GAMMA-RAY BURSTERS. THROUGH DETAILED STUDIES OF INDIVIDUAL SUPERNOVA, AND THROUGH THE CONSTRUCTION OF MODEL GRIDS, WE ARE ABLE TO INFER DEFICIENCIES IN OUR MODELING, IN OUR ATOMIC DATA, AND IN THE PROGENITOR MODELS, AND HENCE MAKE REFINEMENTS SO THAT WE CAN IMPROVE OUR UNDERSTANDING OF ALL SNE CLASSES. PREVIOUS (IUE), CURRENT (HST, CHANDRA, GALEX), AND FUTURE NASA MISSIONS (JAMES WEBB TELESCOPE) DO/WILL PROVIDE A WEALTH OF DATA ON SUPERNOVAE. THE PROPOSED RESEARCH IS RELATED TO STRATEGIC SUBGOAL 3D: "DISCOVER THE ORIGIN, STRUCTURE, EVOLUTION, AND DESTINY OF THE UNIVERSE, AND SEARCH FOR EARTH-LIKE PLANETS." SUPERNOVAE ARE INHERENTLY COUPLED TO THE EVOLUTION OF THE UNIVERSE AND LIFE: THEY CAN TRIGGER STAR FORMATION AND THEY PROVIDE THE RAW MATERIALS (E.G., OXYGEN, SILICON, IRON) FROM WHICH PLANETS AND LIFE FORM -- WE OWE OUR EXISTENCE TO MULTIPLE SUPERNOVA EXPLOSIONS. UNDERSTANDING THE ORIGIN AND STRUCTURE OF SUPERNOVAE IS THUS CRUCIAL FOR UNDERSTANDING THE ORIGIN OF THE ELEMENTS.

doc.ContractDescription: THE IMPRINT OF PATCHY REIONIZATION ON THE COSMIC MICROWAVE BACKGROUND COSMIC REIONIZATION IS A FRONTIER TOPIC IN COSMOLOGY WITH PLENTY OF SCIENTIFIC RICHNESS FOR THEORETICAL AND OBSERVATIONAL EXPLORATIONS. WHAT UNIQUELY MARKS THE EPOCH OF REIONIZATION (EOR) IS THE EMERGENCE OF THE FIRST LUMINOUS SOURCES. STUDYING THE EOR WILL REVEAL HOW THE FIRST GENERATION OF STARS, GALAXIES, AND QUASARS FORMED AND EVOLVED. IT CAN PROVIDE CONSTRAINTS ON COSMOLOGICAL PARAMETERS COMPARABLE TO STUDIES OF THE COSMIC MICROWAVE BACKGROUND (CMB). OVER THE NEXT FEW YEARS, CMB OBSERVATIONS ALONE HAVE THE POTENTIAL TO PROVIDE STRONG CONSTRAINTS ON THE EOR. INHOMOGENEOUS ELECTRON SCATTERING DURING THE EOR GENERATED SECONDARY TEMPERATURE FLUCTUATIONS AND INDUCED E-MODE POLARIZATION IN THE CMB. THE PLANCK SATELLITE WILL HAVE MUCH IMPROVED FULL-SKY MEASUREMENTS OF THE TEMPERATURE AND POLARIZATION POWER SPECTRA COMPARED. THE ATACAMA COSMOLOGY TELESCOPE WITH POLARIZATION (ACTPOL) AND SOUTH POLE TELESCOPE WITH POLARIZATION (SPTPOL) WILL COMPLIMENTARILY PROVIDE HIGHER RESOLUTION AND SENSITIVITY MEASUREMENTS OVER SEVERAL THOUSAND SQUARE DEGREES. THE PROPOSED PROJECT WILL STUDY THE IMPRINT OF COSMIC REIONIZATION ON THE CMB USING DIRECT COSMOLOGICAL (RADIATIVE TRANSFER + HYDRODYNAMIC + N-BODY) SIMULATIONS AND CALIBRATED SEMI-ANALYTICAL MODELS. THE COMPLEXITY OF REIONIZATION REQUIRES HIGH-RESOLUTION SIMULATIONS WITH BETTER PHYSICAL MODELS THAT CAN BE TESTED AGAINST HIGHREDSHIFT OBSERVATIONS. TO MODEL THE OBSERVATIONAL SIGNATURES, FASTER SEMI-ANALYTICAL TECHNIQUES ARE REQUIRED TO MAKE LARGE-SCALE MOCK OBSERVATIONS AND TO EXPLORE THE LARGE PARAMETER SPACE. RADIATION-HYDRODYNAMIC SIMULATIONS WILL BE RUN TO STUDY HOW THE DISTRIBUTION AND PROPERTIES OF RADIATION SOURCES AND SINKS AFFECT THE DETAILED HISTORY OF THE EOR. PARAMETRIC, SEMI-ANALYTICAL MODELS WILL BE USED TO CONSTRUCT LARGE-SCALE MOCK OBSERVATIONS. THE MODEL PARAMETERS WILL BE CALIBRATED AGAINST SIMULATIONS, BUT ARE VARIED AWAY FROM THE FIDUCIAL VALUES TO EXPLORE THE PARAMETER SPACE. THE IMPRINT OF ANISOTROPIC ELECTRON SCATTERING ON THE CMB TEMPERATURE AND POLARIZATION ANISOTROPIES WILL BE MODELED AND QUANTIFIED. KEY OBSERVABLES SUCH AS E-MODE POLARIZATION, PATCHY THOMSON SCATTERING, AND THE KINETIC SUNYAEV-ZEL'DOVICH EFFECT WILL BE THE MAJOR FOCUS. A LARGE DATABASE OF SIMULATIONS, MOCK OBSERVATIONS, FITTING TEMPLATES, AND VISUALIZATIONS WILL BE MADE PUBLICLY AVAILABLE TO THE SCIENTIFIC COMMUNITY TO FACILITATE WIDER COMPARISONS BETWEEN THEORETICAL CALCULATIONS AND OBSERVATIONAL DATA. THE PROPOSED RESEARCH IS IN ACCORDANCE WITH NASA ASTROPHYSICS GOALS WHICH IS BROADLY DEFINED AS TO "DISCOVER HOW THE UNIVERSE WORKS, EXPLORE HOW THE UNIVERSE BEGAN AND DEVELOPED INTO ITS PRESENT FORM, AND SEARCH FOR EARTH-LIKE PLANETS". THE PROPOSAL ATTEMPTS TO ANSWER THE TWO SUB-QUESTIONS: "HOW DO MATTER, ENERGY, SPACE, AND TIME BEHAVE UNDER THE EXTRAORDINARY DIVERSE CONDITIONS OF THE COSMOS?" AND "HOW DID THE UNIVERSE ORIGINATE AND EVOLVE TO PRODUCE THE GALAXIES, STARS, AND PLANETS WE SEE TODAY?" THE PROPOSED WORK ON THE CMB IS RELEVANT TO THE WILKINSON MICROWAVE ANISOTROPY PROBE (WMAP), WHICH IS A NASA MISSION, AND THE PLANCK SATELLITE, WHICH IS A EUROPEAN SPACE AGENCY MISSION WITH NASA PARTICIPATION. THE PROPOSED WORK ON HIGH-REDSHIFT GALAXIES IS RELEVANT TO NASA'S ONGOING HUBBLE SPACE TELESCOPE MISSION AND THE UPCOMING JAMES WEBB SPACE TELESCOPE MISSION.
